Tejveer, fondly referred to as Tej, this morning crashed out of World Rally Championship (WRC) Safari Rally after his monster R5 rolled several times at Kedong.    Tejveer went flat out before his VW GTI Polo nose-dived during the second day of the Safari Rally. Initial reports indicated that Tejveer suffered non-life-threatening injuries after the crash.  He was however airlifted to Nairobi for treatment. His navigator Gareth Dawe also suffered minor injuries.  ‘Vasha’ comes alive as revellers vroom in for the rally action  Frenchman Ogier shows rivals dust at Kasarani stage  Lucky Kenyan fan calls out pace notes for Red Bull driver Fourmaux at Ndulele Shakedown  Blow as 13 Kenyan drivers axed from Safari Rally  In Pictures: WRC Safari Rally flag-off at KICC Following the accident, Rai’s father Jaswant Rai made his way to Aga Khan Hospital.  The business mogul is one of the top Kenyans who lobbied for the return of the Safari Rally to the WRC calendar.  Tej, who is considered a rising star, finished second in the ARC Equator Rally, which was a preamble to the Safari Rally Kenya return to the WRC calendar.  The Kabras Racing Team driver is the younger brother of Menengai Oils Team driver Onkar Rai.      WRC Safari Rally: Kenya to host WRC event in June, Naivasha town to be the nerve center  Mashindano ya Safari Rally siku ya 1; Onka Rai ameongoza mchujo wa kwanza | Zilizala Viwanjani By Ben Ahenda | 1 hour ago By Ochieng Oyugi and Antony Gitonga | 12 hours ago By Ochieng Oyugi | 13 hours ago By Ochieng Oyugi | 18 hours ago